title: Georgia Firm Recalls Beef and Chicken Products Due to Misbranding and Undeclared Allergens
summary: WASHINGTON, Jan. 16, 2015 Kabobs Acquisition Inc., a Lake City, Ga. establishment, is recalling approximately 869 pounds of beef and chicken products due to misbranding and undeclared allergens, the U.S. Department of Agricultures Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) announced today.
